The author has long felt that computer science graduates should know a great deal about computer organization, architecture, and hardware. Further, majors in computer science should be made aware that during their careers as computer scientists they are very likely to encounter situations i.n which 1/0 will not be from or to keyboards, CRTs, disks, tapes, printers, etc. To these ends we have threaded the topics of organization, architecture, and hardware through three two-course sequences at three levels of sophistication.